    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix incomplete QPSK LUT initialization in TM2 transmit diversity\n\n### Summary\nThe `init_modulation_LUT_qam4_tm2_p2()` function was only initializing 16 entries instead of the required 256 entries for 4 QPSK symbols. This caused incorrect modulation mapping when using TM2 transmit diversity with QPSK, leading to degraded throughput and incorrect signal constellation patterns.\n\nThis fix corrects the array sizing and loop bounds to process all 8-bit input combinations.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair1/PHY/LTE_TRANSPORT/dlsch_modulation.c`: \n  - Changed qam4_tm2_p2 array declarations from [8][16] to [8][256]\n  - Updated loop bounds from index<16 to index<256\n  - Fixed bit extraction logic to properly handle all 8 bits for 4 QPSK symbols\n  - Corrected TM2 precoding implementation for 4-symbol mapping\n\n### Reproduction\nTo reproduce the issue:\n1. Configure eNB with TM2 transmit diversity mode\n2. Set modulation to QPSK\n3. Transmit data continuously \n4. Observe degraded BLER performance and constellation distortion\n5. Memory analysis shows only 16 LUT entries were initialized instead of 256\n\nThe symptoms manifest as poor link performance specifically with QPSK in TM2 mode, while 16QAM and 64QAM work correctly since their LUT initialization was already properly implemented.\n"
}